Former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar has said he is still consulting with important persons towards his 2023 presidential ambition. The frontline politician promised to announce his intention at the appropriate time. Atiku had visited former Military President, General Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida (IBB) at his Uphill Residence in Minna, the Niger State capital, where they had closed-door meeting for an hour. The former Vice-President thereafter visited Governor Abubakar Sani Bello to commiserate with the state on the recent killings of some residents by bandits.   Ex-Lagos Gov Ambode breaks silence on 2023     Why I left Atiku, by estranged wife Jennifer     Pension complaints and solutions   Addressing reporters after visiting the governor, Atiku said he was in the state on a courtesy visit, adding that he could not leave without visiting General Babangida. - Advertisement - “I am on a courtesy call. That is all. On the 2023 presidential election, I will let you know at the appropriate time,” he said. Condoling with the government over the insecurity bedevilling the state, Atiku described it as unfortunate and saddening. He stressed that something should be done to address the situation. “I have just discussed the issue of insecurity with the governor. It is a very pathetic situation. In fact, I got a very vivid picture of what is going on in Niger State from the governor. I mean, it is most unfortunate,” Atiku said.